    "department": "Human Resources",
    "description": "WHY HARVEY\n\nAt Harvey, we’re transforming how legal and professional services operate — not incrementally, but end-to-end. By combining frontier agentic AI, an enterprise-grade platform, and deep domain expertise, we’re reshaping how critical knowledge work gets done for decades to come.\n\nThis is a rare chance to help build a generational company at a true inflection point. With 1000+ customers in 60+ countries, strong product-market fit, and world-class investor support, we’re scaling fast and defining a new category in real time. The work is ambitious, the bar is high, and the opportunity for growth — personal, professional, and financial — is unmatched.\n\nOur team is sharp, motivated, and deeply committed to the mission. We move fast, operate with intensity, and take real ownership of the problems we tackle — from early thinking to long-term outcomes. We stay close to our customers — from leadership to engineers — and work together to solve real problems with urgency and care. If you thrive in ambiguity, push for excellence, and want to help shape the future of work alongside others who raise the bar, we invite you to build with us.\n\nAt Harvey, the future of professional services is being written today — and we’re just getting started.\n\n\nROLE OVERVIEW\n\nHarvey is transforming how the world’s best legal professionals work. As we continue to scale, we’re looking for a People Business Partner to support our Product and Design teams, based in San Francisco, with the potential to support additional technical orgs over time.\n\nIn this role, you’ll partner closely with Product and Design leaders to help them build and scale high-performing, high-ownership teams. You’ll work side-by-side with leaders as they navigate growth, evolve their org structures, and operate in an environment where priorities shift quickly.\n\nThis role reports to the Head of People Business Partners and works closely with leaders across the technical org as well as the broader People team. The right person brings strong judgment, can quickly build credibility with technical leaders, and is comfortable operating in a fast-moving, often ambiguous environment.\n\n\n\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL DO\n\nPartner deeply with Product and Design leaders\n\n - Work closely with leaders as they build and scale their teams, advising on org design, team structure, and how to operate effectively through rapid growth and change.\n\nCoach and challenge leaders\n\n - Support leaders in navigating complex people and organizational decisions. Provide direct, thoughtful feedback and help raise the bar on leadership across the org.\n\nDrive performance and accountability\n\n - Partner with managers on performance, feedback, and development, ensuring teams are operating at a high bar and addressing gaps quickly.\n\nNavigate complex people situations\n\n - Handle employee relations matters with sound judgment, balancing empathy for individuals with what’s right for the team and the business.\n\nStay close to the work\n\n - Develop a strong understanding of how Product, Design, and Engineering teams operate, from how decisions are made to where friction exists, and use that context to guide leaders effectively.\n\nOperate in ambiguity\n\n - Help leaders navigate shifting priorities, evolving org structures, and new problem spaces, bringing clarity where things are not yet fully defined.\n\nHelp scale how we work\n\n - Partner with the Head of PBPs and broader People team to evolve and implement practices that support high-performing technical teams.\n\n\n\n\n\nWHAT YOU HAVE\n\n - 6–10+ years of experience in a People Business Partner role, ideally supporting Product, Design, or Engineering teams.\n\n - Experience working with technical leaders - you understand how product and engineering organizations operate and can build credibility quickly.\n\n - Strong judgment and the ability to navigate ambiguity - you’re comfortable operating without perfect information and making decisions in real time.\n\n - Ability to influence and challenge senior leaders in a thoughtful and direct way.\n\n - Experience supporting org design, performance management, and team scaling in high-growth environments.\n\n - High emotional intelligence and strong communication skills, especially in complex or sensitive situations.\n\n - A pragmatic, no-drama approach - you focus on what works for the business and move things forward.\n\n - Ability to work from our San Francisco office at least three days per week.\n\n\n\n\n\nCOMPENSATION\n\n$165,400 - $248,200 USD\n\n\nDEPENDING ON YOUR LOCATION, AN APPLICANT PRIVACY NOTICE MAY APPLY TO YOU. YOU CAN FIND ALL OF OUR APPLICANT PRIVACY NOTICES [HERE https://www.notion.so/harveyai/Harvey-Candidate-Privacy-Policies-319ac3fcdd7a803bb807d5094f249922].\n\n#LI-RB1\n\nHarvey is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of race, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity/expression, national origin, disability, age, genetic information, veteran status, marital status, pregnancy or related condition, or any other basis protected by law.\n\nWe are committed to providing reasonable accommodations to applicants with disabilities, and requests can be made by emailing accommodations@harvey.ai",
